   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_157571_1842_08_27_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <date when="1842-08-27"/>Aug<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1842 <lb/>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  Sir
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Your letter from its ability<lb/>
               and air of frankness and<lb/>
               candor makes me wish<lb/>
               that it were in my power<lb/>
               to assist you - </p>
            <lb/>
            <p>  From my own funds<lb/>
               it is not in my power - But<lb/>
               one of my brothers - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#PakeX3">Pakenham</persName>
               <lb/>
               who is grateful for your <choice>
                  <orig>mo-<lb/>
                  thers</orig>
                  <reg>mothers</reg>
               </choice> kindness to him when<lb/>
               a boy, also to M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntX1">Hunter</persName>
               <lb/>
               could and would assist you<lb/>
               with the ten pounds you say<lb/>
               would be so essentially <choice>
                  <orig>servi-<lb/>
                  ceable</orig>
                  <reg>serviceable</reg>
               </choice> to you, if <add>you</add> can comply<lb/>
               with the conditions <del>on</del> which<lb/>
               we require - If you will<lb/>
               allow me to mention the<lb/>
               matter to M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntX1">Hunter</persName> and<lb/>
               if he <hi rend="underline">underwrites</hi> your letter<lb/>
               - It cannot but do you credit<lb/>
               that he should see that letter<lb/>
               if the statements be <del>
                  <unclear/>
               </del>
               <lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_157571_1842_08_27_page02.jpg"/>
               
               correct - And you will not<lb/>
               I hope take it ill that <del>
                  <unclear/>
               </del>
               <lb/>
               I who am as you observe<lb/>
               an absolute stranger to you<lb/>
               should wish to refer as strang<unclear>ers</unclear>
               <lb/>
               generally are desired to do<lb/>
               upon such occasions for <choice>
                  <orig>fur-<lb/>
                  ther</orig>
                  <reg>further</reg>
               </choice> information to some<lb/>
               common friend - From<lb/>
               long knowledge of your<lb/>
               step father M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntX1">Hunter</persName> I have<lb/>
               perfect reliance upon his <choice>
                  <orig>can-<lb/>
                  dor</orig>
                  <reg>candor</reg>
               </choice> and his justice and upon<lb/>
               his friendly disposition towards<lb/>
               all connected with him </p>
            <lb/>
            <p> If you permit me so to<lb/>
               do I will enclose your letter<lb/>
               to Mr. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntX1">Hunter</persName> and if he simply<lb/>
               puts his name to it and<lb/>
               returns it to me my brothers<lb/>
               discuss for so now in my hands<lb/>
               shall be in yours by return of<lb/>
               post -<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               I am Sir<lb/> 
               Your obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
               <lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
         </div>
      </body>
